<p>I need to retrieve the element name that is like this "*-Font" and then retrieve the attribute values.</p>  <p>Here is the linq used...</p>  <pre><code>Dim categories = From dc as xelement In Xml.DescendantsAndSelf("defaults") _ let Id = lw.name _ Where Id = "*-Font" _ let FontFamily = lw.attribute("font-family").value _ let FontSize = lw.attribute("font-size").value _ Select Id, FontFamily, FontSize </code></pre>  <p>Here is the xml sample...</p>  <pre><code>&lt;defaults&gt;     &lt;scaling&gt;1&lt;/scaling&gt;     &lt;page-layout&gt;2&lt;/page-layout&gt;     &lt;system-layout&gt;3&lt;/system-layout&gt;     &lt;appearance&gt;4&lt;/appearance&gt;     &lt;default-font font-family="Arial" font-size="20.4"/&gt;     &lt;word-font font-family="Times New Roman" font-size="10.2"/&gt; &lt;/defaults&gt; </code></pre>  <p>This query fails with... Operator 'Like' is not defined for types 'System.Xml.Linq.XName' and 'String'.</p>  <p>I've done a net search and found nothing for Linq to xml and the Like operator.</p>  <p>Ok, so how can I retrieve all the element names Like "*-Font".</p>